    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Just use <a href="http://php.net/usort" rel="noreferrer"><code>usort</code></a>:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">compare_some_objects</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span></span>) </span>{ <span class="hljs-comment">// Make sure to give this a more meaningful name!</span>
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;id - <span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;id;
}

<span class="hljs-comment">// ...</span>

<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>, <span class="hljs-string">'compare_some_objects'</span>);
</code></pre>

<p>If you have PHP 5.3 or higher, you can also use an anonymous function:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>, function(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>) { <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;id - <span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;id; });
</code></pre>
    </div>
